text: Luo Zhenyu (August 8, 1866 - May 14, 1940), courtesy name Shuyun (叔蘊), was a Chinese classical scholar, philologist, epigrapher, antiquarian. He supported the Qing dynasty, even after it fell. Category:1940 deaths Category:1866 births Category:Pages with unreviewed translations
title: Luo Zhenyu
